{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01B1UcfE9xDDduBWAK8D6jpq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have everything. Let me write the plan to a temp file and create the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1340,"cache_read_input_tokens":29580,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1340},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8434144e-e398-4483-8bbb-8fa0262c5972","uuid":"7a7147dd-6786-4e5b-b586-3f24d2f167af","request_id":"req_011Cc6irW1P6huwtR23hwAoh"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01B1UcfE9xDDduBWAK8D6jpq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01U5b2Dc4JTfe5b2vhTk16Kt","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/ray-change-plan.md","content":"# Ray Cluster Migration Plan\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-16  \n**Namespace:** ray  \n**Status:** DRAFT — for review only. No changes have been applied.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State\n\n### Deployments\n\n| Deployment | Replicas | Image |\n|---|---|---|\n| ray-head | 1 | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 |\n| ray-worker | 3 | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 |\n\nBoth deployments have **no resource requests or limits** configured (`resources: {}`), which leaves pods unconstrained and may cause OOM evictions or CPU starvation under load.\n\n### Services\n\n| Service | Type | Ports |\n|---|---|---|\n| ray-head | ClusterIP (10.96.224.130) | 6379/TCP (gcs), 8265/TCP (dashboard) |\n\nThe Ray dashboard is exposed on port 8265 of the `ray-head` ClusterIP service. It is reachable only from within the cluster (no NodePort or LoadBalancer). There is no separate dashboard service.\n\n### Summary of non-default configuration already in place\n- Worker replicas scaled up from default 1 → **3**\n- Dashboard port (8265) added to the `ray-head` Service alongside GCS (6379)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Proposed Changes for Next Upgrade Window\n\n### 2a. Image Upgrade: 2.9.0 → 2.10.0\n\nUpgrade both `ray-head` and `ray-worker` from `rayproject/ray:2.9.0` to `rayproject/ray:2.10.0`.  \nRationale: 2.10 includes runtime environment improvements, autoscaler fixes, and dashboard stability patches relevant to this cluster's usage profile.\n\n### 2b. Add Resource Requests and Limits\n\nSet explicit CPU/memory budgets to prevent noisy-neighbour evictions and give the scheduler accurate placement information.\n\n**ray-head** (GCS server + dashboard; latency-sensitive, not compute-heavy):\n- requests: cpu=500m, memory=1Gi\n- limits:   cpu=2,    memory=2Gi\n\n**ray-worker** (task execution; may be CPU/memory intensive):\n- requests: cpu=1,    memory=2Gi\n- limits:   cpu=4,    memory=4Gi\n\n### 2c. Scale Workers from 3 → 4\n\nAdd a fourth worker replica to increase parallel task throughput and provide headroom during rolling updates (one worker will be temporarily unavailable during the image upgrade rollout).\n\n### 2d. Expose Dashboard via a Dedicated NodePort Service\n\nCreate a separate `ray-dashboard` NodePort service so the dashboard is reachable from outside the cluster without `kubectl port-forward`. The existing `ray-head` ClusterIP service is left unchanged.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Proposed kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN — review only)\n\n### Step 1: Upgrade ray-head image and set resource limits\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-head ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\nkubectl -n ray patch deploy/ray-head --type=merge -p '{\n  \"spec\": {\n    \"template\": {\n      \"spec\": {\n        \"containers\": [{\n          \"name\": \"ray-head\",\n          \"resources\": {\n            \"requests\": {\"cpu\": \"500m\", \"memory\": \"1Gi\"},\n            \"limits\":   {\"cpu\": \"2\",    \"memory\": \"2Gi\"}\n          }\n        }]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}'\n```\n\n### Step 2: Upgrade ray-worker image, set resource limits, and scale to 4 replicas\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\nkubectl -n ray patch deploy/ray-worker --type=merge -p '{\n  \"spec\": {\n    \"replicas\": 4,\n    \"template\": {\n      \"spec\": {\n        \"containers\": [{\n          \"name\": \"ray-worker\",\n          \"resources\": {\n            \"requests\": {\"cpu\": \"1\",  \"memory\": \"2Gi\"},\n            \"limits\":   {\"cpu\": \"4\",  \"memory\": \"4Gi\"}\n          }\n        }]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}'\n```\n\n### Step 3: Create dedicated NodePort service for the Ray dashboard\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray apply -f - <<'EOF'\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: ray-dashboard\n  namespace: ray\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: dashboard-service\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: ray\nspec:\n  type: NodePort\n  selector:\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: head\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: ray\n    bench.ray.cluster: ray\n  ports:\n    - name: dashboard\n      port: 8265\n      targetPort: 8265\n      nodePort: 30265\nEOF\n```\n\n### Step 4: Verify rollout completion\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray get svc\n```\n\n### Rollback (if needed)\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray delete svc ray-dashboard\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| Worker OOMKill during image pull under load | Medium | Scale to 4 replicas before image upgrade so cluster retains capacity |\n| GCS server restart causes task failures | Low | ray-head rolling update briefly interrupts GCS; schedule in a low-traffic window |\n| nodePort 30265 conflicts with existing allocation | Low | Verify `kubectl get svc -A | grep 30265` before applying |\n| 2.9 → 2.10 protocol incompatibility | Low | Both head and worker must be upgraded atomically in the same window |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Validation Checklist (post-upgrade)\n\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray get deploy` shows ray-head=1/1 and ray-worker=4/4 READY\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray get pods` — all pods Running, no CrashLoopBackOff\n- [ ] Ray dashboard reachable at `http://<node-ip>:30265`\n- [ ] Submit a test Ray task and confirm it completes successfully\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray top pods` — resource usage within the new limits\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1340,"cache_read_input_tokens":29580,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1340},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8434144e-e398-4483-8bbb-8fa0262c5972","uuid":"dd14b06f-65eb-4c9f-9195-1d1ed83ab194","request_id":"req_011Cc6irW1P6huwtR23hwAoh"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U5b2Dc4JTfe5b2vhTk16Kt","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /tmp/ray-change-plan.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8434144e-e398-4483-8bbb-8fa0262c5972","uuid":"76c63025-1b1a-452d-b4d9-ffd3f8b30896","timestamp":"2026-06-16T09:44:28.434Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/tmp/ray-change-plan.md","content":"# Ray Cluster Migration Plan\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-16  \n**Namespace:** ray  \n**Status:** DRAFT — for review only. No changes have been applied.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State\n\n### Deployments\n\n| Deployment | Replicas | Image |\n|---|---|---|\n| ray-head | 1 | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 |\n| ray-worker | 3 | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 |\n\nBoth deployments have **no resource requests or limits** configured (`resources: {}`), which leaves pods unconstrained and may cause OOM evictions or CPU starvation under load.\n\n### Services\n\n| Service | Type | Ports |\n|---|---|---|\n| ray-head | ClusterIP (10.96.224.130) | 6379/TCP (gcs), 8265/TCP (dashboard) |\n\nThe Ray dashboard is exposed on port 8265 of the `ray-head` ClusterIP service. It is reachable only from within the cluster (no NodePort or LoadBalancer). There is no separate dashboard service.\n\n### Summary of non-default configuration already in place\n- Worker replicas scaled up from default 1 → **3**\n- Dashboard port (8265) added to the `ray-head` Service alongside GCS (6379)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Proposed Changes for Next Upgrade Window\n\n### 2a. Image Upgrade: 2.9.0 → 2.10.0\n\nUpgrade both `ray-head` and `ray-worker` from `rayproject/ray:2.9.0` to `rayproject/ray:2.10.0`.  \nRationale: 2.10 includes runtime environment improvements, autoscaler fixes, and dashboard stability patches relevant to this cluster's usage profile.\n\n### 2b. Add Resource Requests and Limits\n\nSet explicit CPU/memory budgets to prevent noisy-neighbour evictions and give the scheduler accurate placement information.\n\n**ray-head** (GCS server + dashboard; latency-sensitive, not compute-heavy):\n- requests: cpu=500m, memory=1Gi\n- limits:   cpu=2,    memory=2Gi\n\n**ray-worker** (task execution; may be CPU/memory intensive):\n- requests: cpu=1,    memory=2Gi\n- limits:   cpu=4,    memory=4Gi\n\n### 2c. Scale Workers from 3 → 4\n\nAdd a fourth worker replica to increase parallel task throughput and provide headroom during rolling updates (one worker will be temporarily unavailable during the image upgrade rollout).\n\n### 2d. Expose Dashboard via a Dedicated NodePort Service\n\nCreate a separate `ray-dashboard` NodePort service so the dashboard is reachable from outside the cluster without `kubectl port-forward`. The existing `ray-head` ClusterIP service is left unchanged.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Proposed kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN — review only)\n\n### Step 1: Upgrade ray-head image and set resource limits\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-head ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\nkubectl -n ray patch deploy/ray-head --type=merge -p '{\n  \"spec\": {\n    \"template\": {\n      \"spec\": {\n        \"containers\": [{\n          \"name\": \"ray-head\",\n          \"resources\": {\n            \"requests\": {\"cpu\": \"500m\", \"memory\": \"1Gi\"},\n            \"limits\":   {\"cpu\": \"2\",    \"memory\": \"2Gi\"}\n          }\n        }]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}'\n```\n\n### Step 2: Upgrade ray-worker image, set resource limits, and scale to 4 replicas\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\nkubectl -n ray patch deploy/ray-worker --type=merge -p '{\n  \"spec\": {\n    \"replicas\": 4,\n    \"template\": {\n      \"spec\": {\n        \"containers\": [{\n          \"name\": \"ray-worker\",\n          \"resources\": {\n            \"requests\": {\"cpu\": \"1\",  \"memory\": \"2Gi\"},\n            \"limits\":   {\"cpu\": \"4\",  \"memory\": \"4Gi\"}\n          }\n        }]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}'\n```\n\n### Step 3: Create dedicated NodePort service for the Ray dashboard\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray apply -f - <<'EOF'\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: ray-dashboard\n  namespace: ray\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: dashboard-service\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: ray\nspec:\n  type: NodePort\n  selector:\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: head\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: ray\n    bench.ray.cluster: ray\n  ports:\n    - name: dashboard\n      port: 8265\n      targetPort: 8265\n      nodePort: 30265\nEOF\n```\n\n### Step 4: Verify rollout completion\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray get svc\n```\n\n### Rollback (if needed)\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray delete svc ray-dashboard\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| Worker OOMKill during image pull under load | Medium | Scale to 4 replicas before image upgrade so cluster retains capacity |\n| GCS server restart causes task failures | Low | ray-head rolling update briefly interrupts GCS; schedule in a low-traffic window |\n| nodePort 30265 conflicts with existing allocation | Low | Verify `kubectl get svc -A | grep 30265` before applying |\n| 2.9 → 2.10 protocol incompatibility | Low | Both head and worker must be upgraded atomically in the same window |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Validation Checklist (post-upgrade)\n\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray get deploy` shows ray-head=1/1 and ray-worker=4/4 READY\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray get pods` — all pods Running, no CrashLoopBackOff\n- [ ] Ray dashboard reachable at `http://<node-ip>:30265`\n- [ ] Submit a test Ray task and confirm it completes successfully\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray top pods` — resource usage within the new limits\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
